<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-05-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-05-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="399" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d399">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">White</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy
                                        of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-05-30"><hi rend="italic">May 30,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>German Government has not the slightest objection to having Cuban
                            interests represented for the present as heretofore.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>